<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36084g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36084g">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36084g"> 84(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> slype / calefactory</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Cathedral precincts are interesting. South of the remains of the old chapter-house, of beautiful moulded thirteenth-century work, discovered in 1886 by Sir Thomas Drew, lay the <i>calefactory</i> of the old monastic foundation, separated from the former by the <i>Slype</i>. This was the site of the passage long known as &ldquo;Hell&rdquo;. <small> Samuel A. Ossory Fitzpatrick, <a name="SAOF" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SAOF"><cite title="source">Dublin: A Historical and Topographical Account of the City</cite></a> (1907) 30</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
